We recommended that Management direct the SWMO, together with the MPDC, to:
23) Ensure compliance with the requirements of the EMB V and other related agencies to facilitate the completion and approval of the Solid Waste Management Plan and the development of the proposed sanitary landfill in the Municipality;
24) Conduct continuing information, education, and communication (IEC) campaign to raise awareness about the pertinent provisions of R.A. 9003, particularly on waste segregation at source and waste diversion;
25) Coordinate with the Barangay Ecological Solid Waste Management Council (BESWMC) to ensure that the Municipal Programs on solid waste management are properly communicated and observed at the barangay level;
26) Require the barangays, through its BESWMC, to ensure that the mandate of Executive Order No. 06 and Executive Order No. 12, series of 2023, are strictly observed by the households and various institutions in the Municipality;
27) Direct the BESWMC to comply with the reporting requirements of the Municipality and other related agencies to facilitate the monitoring of its solid waste management activities and to timely communicate and address their concerns; and
28) Submit the ECC for the construction of a sanitary landfill.

We recommended that management:
35) Revisit the IRR on TAWO for clear, comprehensive, and well-defined guidelines, procedures, and parameters to ensure that only eligible indigent beneficiaries were given the type, kind, and amount of assistance they needed after the assessment, validation, and recommendation of the MSWDO;
36) Initiate a comprehensive review of the TAWO and all other assistance to the poor, vulnerable, and marginalized individuals and families so that the financial aid and other assistance programs attain its purpose, and its benefits redound to as many qualified and needy clients the fund can accommodate;
37) Through the MSWDO, conduct a prior study, screening, verification, assessment, and recommendation of the qualified recipients of the program and install and implement a control mechanism that would monitor the beneficiaries and assistance, qualification, and eligibility of beneficiaries and funds available for disbursement; and
38) Explain the burial assistance provided to the family of the late municipal official, despite their non-qualification within the set parameters.

